<item>
 <title>Carbon Capture and Storage: Prospects after Paris</title>
 <link>http://www.chinafaqs.org/blog-posts/carbon-capture-and-storage-prospects-after-paris</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-filefield field-field-image&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;img src=&quot;http://www.chinafaqs.org/files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/Chinese%20coal%20plant.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; title=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;160&quot; height=&quot;120&quot; class=&quot;imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default&quot;/&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-author&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    Katie Lebling and Xiaoliang Yang        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;This post &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wri.org/blog/2016/04/carbon-capture-and-storage-prospects-after-paris&quot;&gt;originally appeared&lt;/a&gt; on WRI&amp;#8217;s Insights blog:&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Momentum for climate action &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.wri.org/blog/2016/04/commitment-action-signs-progress-paris-climate-talks&quot;&gt;has surged&lt;/a&gt; since the Paris Agreement in December, with increased investment in clean, renewable energy and new energy technologies. But will the Agreement give a needed boost to carbon capture and storage? Known as CCS, this suite of technologies aims to keep climate-warming carbon dioxide out of the atmosphere, acting as a bridge to a lower-carbon future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.chinafaqs.org/blog-posts/carbon-capture-and-storage-prospects-after-paris&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;read more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
